 The government has no reliable tracking system, but health officials say food-borne diseases account for up to 30 million cases of illness and 9,000 deaths a year. 
 There have been many large outbreaks of food-borne illness in the last year, including one just last week that made a New York woman ill and resulted in the recall of 172,000 pounds of ground beef patties. 
 Congress has failed to address legislation to give the Food and Drug Administration greater authority to halt imports of fruits, vegetables and other food products that are produced under safety conditions that do not match our own strict standards.